gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: Census_County_TIGER00_IN contains locations for all Indiana counties and contains census data for each county. Data is from U.S. Department of Commerce, U.S. Census Bureau, Census 2000 SF1 tables.

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: BROAD, GENERAL information for planning, development, and research in Indiana

gmd:credit.gco:CharacterString: Indiana Statewide GIS database was produced under an Indiana Department of Transportation contract. Data is from U.S. Department of Commerce, U.S. Census Bureau, Census 2000 Tiger Line Files and SF1 tables. Polygons were obtained from a county boundary shapefile produced by the Indiana Geological Survey. US Census Bureau requests 'Acknowledgment of the U.S. Census Bureau would be appreciated for products derived from these files.' Indiana Geological Survey requests 'Indiana Geological Survey be cited in any products generated from this data. The following source citation should be included: [LANDSURVEY_COUNTY_POLY_IN: County Boundaries of Indiana (Indiana Geological Survey, 1:24,000, Polygon Shapefile)].'

gmd:measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: Indiana Geological Survey metadata reports - "A check was made for dangling nodes and none were detected."

Indiana Geological Survey metadata reports - "A check was made to verify that the county boundaries are continuous and are identical to the county boundaries contained in IN_LANDSURVEY. Census SF1 table attributes were joined for all counties."

Indiana Geological Survey metadata reports- "All county names contained in the fields named "NAME_U" and "NAME_L" were checked against the USGS 7.5-minute quadrangles. The prefix code contained in the field named "NCAPC" was checked against the AccessIndiana Indiana Bureau of Motor Vehicles license plates and titles county prefixes listed on license plates. US Census Bureau makes no claim as to the accuracy of its SF1 table attributes. See Census Technical Documentation for more information."

Indiana Geological Survey metadata reports - "Accuracy is no better than that of the source material. The vector lines contained were corrected to DRG raster lines at an on-screen scale of 1:5,000 or better. Polygon data is a digital representation of land survey features as represented on the USGS 1:24,000 digital raster graphic (DRG) series."
Vertical accuracy was not a factor in the digital production of the data set. No quantitative tests were performed.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Bernardin, Lochmueller and Associates joined SF1 tabular data to the unique name code field in the County Boundary file.

This metadata was pre-parsed and parsed using CNS (Chew and Spit. v 2.6.1) and MP (Metadata Parser, v 2.7.1) software written by Peter N. Schweitzer (United States Geological Survey). The errors generated by MP were all addressed and corrected, except that no values were assigned to "Abscissa_Resolution" and "Ordinate_Resolution."
